properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 26 at 4:33AM PST until January 27 at 12:00PM PST by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Areas of northwest to north winds 20 to 30 mph with gusts
to 45 mph.

* WHERE...Santa Clarita Valley.

* WHEN...From 3 PM this afternoon to noon PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and
make driving difficult, especially for drivers of high profile
vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages
may result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Gusty winds will affect travel on
Interstate 5 and Highways 14 and 126.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects such as lawn furniture.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 3 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO NOON PST MONDAY
